{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"self-waltz-ace","description":"RISK 2 (over-cap growth). `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/applier.py` grew +117 LOC to 918 (re-heated — it was the prior 9.0× churn thrash leader). Its `_apply_batch` is a 386-LOC body at nesting depth 7. Split along the EXISTING dispatch-table seam, not by line count.\n\n## Why\nThe documented remedy (`docs/architecture.md:222`) — separate the apply-dispatch table from the per-action handlers — was never executed.\n\n## What — careful split along the dispatch seam\n- Extract the per-action mutation handlers (the bodies dispatched per mutation kind inside `_apply_batch`, `:533-918`) into a NEW sibling `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/apply_handlers.py`.\n- Keep `applier.py` as the dispatcher/sequencer: HEAD-pin drift recheck loop → dispatch → record → manifest-write tail. Extract the per-mutation step (drift recheck + dispatch + record) into a helper so nesting drops to <=4.\n- CRITICAL invariant to preserve: abort-without-further-Jira-calls on drift, and the idempotent apply contract.\n\n## Scope\nIn: handler extraction + nesting reduction; the manifest stale-doc TODO (`applier.py:4-15` references a never-created `retry.py` and a wrong LOC figure) should be corrected/removed as part of this. Out: changing apply semantics or the subprocess boundary.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `apply_handlers.py` created (>100 LOC) holding per-action handlers; `applier.py` is the dispatcher.\n- [ ] `_apply_batch` nesting depth <= 4 and materially shorter.\n- [ ] `applier.py` ideally drops below 800 (if so, remove from the allowlist); if not, the allowlist + architecture-doc remedy row are updated to reflect the new structure.\n- [ ] The stale `retry.py`/LOC TODO at `applier.py:4-15` is corrected or removed.\n- [ ] Apply/idempotency + drift-abort tests pass unchanged.","id":"da53-c8d4-feba-4584","parent_id":"5ca8-5993-ca83-40f1","priority":1,"tags":["audit-2026-06-27","oss-remediation"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Risk 2: split applier.py dispatch table from per-action handlers"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782605241534137001,"uuid":"bfdb5d1b-05a1-4268-8fc3-f1ed4114a1dc"}